History
In the gardens of an Oxford College in Victorian England, Alice and her two older sisters are playing fancy dress with one of the young tutors, Mr Dodgson. Soon afterwards, the college prepares for an important visitor, Queen Victoria. When she arrives she is very haughty but also very interested in Mr Dodgson, who she knows to write under the name M-^QLewis CarrollM-^R. 
